<h1>Creating block</h1>
<p>Builder allows you to create, configure and add own blocks.</p>

<h2>Where to</h2>
<p>
    Creating a block is very simple.
    First - create a folder <code>qoob/blocks/name</code> where <code>name</code> - your block's name in lowercase.
</p>

<h2>Basic file structure</h2>
<pre><code>template.hbs     //Handlebars file 
settings.json   //Connection field for block
preview.png     //preview image block
</code></pre>

<h2>Adding styling to your block on the frontend</h2>
<p>
    To customize styling for your block just add to file <code>wp-content/themes/pizza/css/main.css</code>
    Place styling for your block in this file which would be used on the frontend.
</p>

<h2>File name/template.hbs</h2>

