<h2>File name/settings.json</h2>
<p>Each block should have json file. It describes type fields and other parameters. JSON array return an array of key=>value params.</p>

<h3>List of keys</h3>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>key</th>
<th>type</th>
<th>Description</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>name</td>
<td>String</td>
<td>the name attribute specifies the name of an &lt;input&gt; element.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>label</td>
<td>String</td>
<td>title field</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>type</td>
<td>String</td>
<td>name of field, it is determined by field</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>default</td>
<td>String</td>
<td>default parameter fields</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>options</td>
<td>Array\String</td>
<td>default options fields, if need</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>settings</td>
<td>Array</td>
<td>subfields of field</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>

<h3>Example</h3>
<pre><code class="javascript">[{
    "name": "header",
    "label": "Header",
    "type": "text",
    "default": "contact us"
},{
    "name": "border_color",
    "label": "Border color",
    "type": "select",
    "default": "green",
    "options": [{
            "id": "green", "val": "green", "select": "true"
        }, {
            "id": "yellow", "val": "yellow"
        }]
},{
    "name": "text-btn",
    "label": "Text button",
    "type": "text",
    "default": "sign in"
}]</code></pre>

